The Senate of the University of Lagos has elected Prof. Folasade Ogunsola as the Acting Vice-Chancellor of the institution. According to the Nation, Ogunsola polled 135 votes compared to Prof. Ben Oghojafor’s 31 votes. It was also reported that one vote was declared void while a total of 167 Professors were at the Senate meeting. Oghojafor who is the Deputy Vice-Chancellor Management Services was also the first woman to be elected Provost College of Medicine, University of Lagos before she became a DVC. Details shortly…